            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-52616",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "avahi: Avahi Wide-Area DNS Predictable Transaction IDs"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in the Avahi-daemon, where it initializes DNS transaction IDs randomly only once at startup, incrementing them sequentially after that. This predictable behavior facilitates DNS spoofing attacks, allowing attackers to guess transaction IDs."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-52616",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-52616\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: libavahi-common3\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2024-52616](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-52616)\nA flaw was found in the Avahi-daemon, where it initializes DNS transaction IDs randomly only once at startup, incrementing them sequentially after that. This predictable behavior facilitates DNS spoofing attacks, allowing attackers to guess transaction IDs.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-52616**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|libavahi-common3||[CVE-2024-52616](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-52616)|\n\nA flaw was found in the Avahi-daemon, where it initializes DNS transaction IDs randomly only once at startup, incrementing them sequentially after that. This predictable behavior facilitates DNS spoofing attacks, allowing attackers to guess transaction IDs."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "2.0",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "LOW"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-4046",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "glibc: glibc: Denial of Service via iconv() function with specific character sets"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The iconv() function in the GNU C Library versions 2.43 and earlier may crash due to an assertion failure when converting inputs from the IBM1390 or IBM1399 character sets, which may be used to remotely crash an application.\n\n\n\nThis vulnerability can be trivially mitigated by removing the IBM1390 and IBM1399 character sets from systems that do not need them."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-4046",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-4046\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: libc6\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-4046](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-4046)\nThe iconv() function in the GNU C Library versions 2.43 and earlier may crash due to an assertion failure when converting inputs from the IBM1390 or IBM1399 character sets, which may be used to remotely crash an application.\n\n\n\nThis vulnerability can be trivially mitigated by removing the IBM1390 and IBM1399 character sets from systems that do not need them.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-4046**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|libc6||[CVE-2026-4046](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-4046)|\n\nThe iconv() function in the GNU C Library versions 2.43 and earlier may crash due to an assertion failure when converting inputs from the IBM1390 or IBM1399 character sets, which may be used to remotely crash an application.\n\n\n\nThis vulnerability can be trivially mitigated by removing the IBM1390 and IBM1399 character sets from systems that do not need them."
              },
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "5.5",
                "tags": [
