            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-4437",
              "name": "OsPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "glibc: glibc: Incorrect DNS response parsing via crafted DNS server response"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Calling gethostbyaddr or gethostbyaddr_r with a configured nsswitch.conf that specifies the library's DNS backend in the GNU C Library version 2.34 to version 2.43 could, with a crafted response from the configured DNS server, result in a violation of the DNS specification that causes the application to treat a non-answer section of the DNS response as a valid answer."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-4437",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-4437\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: libc6\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2026-4437](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-4437)\nCalling gethostbyaddr or gethostbyaddr_r with a configured nsswitch.conf that specifies the library's DNS backend in the GNU C Library version 2.34 to version 2.43 could, with a crafted response from the configured DNS server, result in a violation of the DNS specification that causes the application to treat a non-answer section of the DNS response as a valid answer.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-4437**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|libc6||[CVE-2026-4437](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-4437)|\n\nCalling gethostbyaddr or gethostbyaddr_r with a configured nsswitch.conf that specifies the library's DNS backend in the GNU C Library version 2.34 to version 2.43 could, with a crafted response from the configured DNS server, result in a violation of the DNS specification that causes the application to treat a non-answer section of the DNS response as a valid answer."
              },
